                <note rend="inline" type="source">838.5045/20: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the High
                        Commissioner in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Russell</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-12-09T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 9, 1929—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>68. We feel strongly that landing of Marines is to be avoided if possible and
                    that it would very seriously adversely affect our relations with all Latin
                    America. Therefore the <hi rend="italic">Wright</hi> instructed to <pb
                        facs="0317" n="199" xml:id="pg_199"/> wait twenty-five miles off Port au
                    Prince morning December 10 pending orders. If reply to our 67 is received from
                    you we will issue orders here. If actual violence going on and situation
                    decidedly worse you can give orders direct to the <hi rend="italic">Wright.</hi>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
